when should u stop laying on ur stomach im weeks along and when i go to bed i lay down on my side but it takes me a while to get comfortable i usually wake up on my stomach but im not putting any pressure directly on my stomach i will have my legs kind of pulled up and my arms underneath my chest and thats where most of the pressure is how can i try and get myself to stay sleeping on my side the rule of thumb here is actually pretty simple you should stop sleeping on your stomach when it becomes uncomfortable for you the baby's well cushioned and at weeks you shouldn't have a problem sleeping on your stomach i was able to until about weeks at which point it seems like my stomach got huge overnight but as soon as i found out i was pregnant i started getting used to sleeping on my side i am a big fan of stomach sleeping but i knew if i didn't start sleeping on my side early on in the pregnancy i wouldn't be able to sleep at all later on now at weeks i usually sleep fairly well my body pillow is my best friend i suggest you invest in one mine's just a cheap one from walmart but it does the trick can't wait to be able to sleep on my stomach again though good luck Mattress Professional wrestling holds Aerial (dance move) Breastfeeding EastEnders Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Stomach cancer Knots Landing Kurt Cobain Marilyn Monroe Friends Equine conformation Days of our Lives Professional wrestling throws Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Piccolo Junior Saga Naval mine Humphrey Bogart The Big Sleep Reservoir Dogs Strap-on dildo Professional wrestling attacks Sleep apnea Theory of conduct Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 The Shining (film) Breech birth Public transport Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Meat Loaf Skateboarding trick Social rule The Contender (television series) Adjustable gastric band Suicide methods Sin City Breaststroke Jam (TV series) Neighbours Urinary incontinence Pregnancy Obstetrics Wal-Mart Dog training Psoriasis Sleeping Murder Main characters of Fullm